<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-CEB0B358-F9CC-4CB3-928B-03878F8B8A01" version="2" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-CEB0B358-F9CC-4CB3-928B-03878F8B8A01" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">02 The function of the ink tank</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-34C6A3E5-E809-4139-80CC-275A8CCF9EDC"><p class="- topic/p ">The ink tank contains the ink supply for the system. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-A04C3701-20A0-469F-9C9D-C3C1F6D4969C" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">The ink tank</title><p class="- topic/p ">All ink tanks are the same and after removal they have to be treated as chemical waste. 
</p><table id="TABLE_11FB3CFFB3374A6DBDD9BACACD85E01F" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Additional information 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">A = 2 ink tubes 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">B = Refill connection 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">C = 2 ink tubes: 1 to the ink pump and 1 is blocked. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">D = mixer motor 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">E = Mixing shaft 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">F = Ventilation filter 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">G = Mixer blade 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">H = Ink tank 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="FIG_1839F467260042629190AE905C9CB3BF" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6DF11D08-DE5E-4E5F-83B7-C664CBFCD8F9-low.png" id="IMAGE_199BEE7A16384498809087671266FACB" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6DF11D08-DE5E-4E5F-83B7-C664CBFCD8F9-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-F5034822-753A-4C8B-A7CD-E44CE7EBD702" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Description</title><p class="- topic/p "> Electrical diagram intermediate reservoir 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See: 
<xref keyref="02ELEC02" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-CBB1EC6F-9A16-42A5-92BA-084E96D293DB.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 02 Electrical diagram intermediate reservoir?>02 Electrical diagram intermediate reservoir</xref> 
</p><table id="GUID-44CC9D37-524C-4240-A579-9C6FC3D85313" pgwide="1" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="80*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Function 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Description 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Ink tank 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">There are 5 ink tanks present in the system. There is one ink tank for each color. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> For their positions in the system see : 
<xref keyref="02COMP01" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-D352B02B-5AEB-45E0-94B7-E1A94045F576.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 02 The components of Ink system?>Mapping pumps to printheads</xref> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Each ink tank can hold a maximum of 2.65 liter of ink. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Mixer 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The ink in the tank contains a mixer to keep the ink supply lump free. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The mixer motor (D) drives the mixer blade (G) inside the tank. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Ink level sensors 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 Sensors are mounted behind each ink tank. These sensors detect the ink level in the tank. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">We can detect: 
</p><ul id="UL_FAC5EEF1129A4D52828D26AF4BBFBB41" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_E4DE8049A05B4A4C9DEC4FD4819ABCFB" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Ink tank full. 
</p></li><li id="LI_9BE0FB30F0AC4A64A9BBB678CE6F642E" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Ink tank half full. 
</p></li><li id="LI_6159D377AF804E358DFE7F731113CC26" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Ink tank almost empty. 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">For detailed information see : 
<xref keyref="02FUNC02" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-B182E6B2-C192-49EF-A460-6AE139F1F6CD.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 02 The function of the ink level sensors?>02 The function of the ink level sensors</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Refill LED 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> A LED, at the front side of the ink supply unit, above each of the 5 ink tanks, indicates if a new refill bottle can be inserted. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Refill connection 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The cap of the ink reservoir contains a refill opening. The refill ink bottle is positioned above this opening. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Ink tubes 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 Metal ink tubes (A) are positioned inside the tank. One of them is used. These tubes almost reach the bottom of the ink tank which makes it possible to almost completely empty the tank. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The ink pump transport the ink from the tube (C) to the printhead. The second ink tube is blocked (not used). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">For detailed information see : 
<xref keyref="02FUNC05" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-0743CE4B-4B8E-4315-889B-B4B37348F19F.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="concept"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 02 The function of the ink tubes and pumps?>02 The function of the ink tubes and pumps</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Ventilation filter 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">A ventilation filter (F) is positioned in the cap of the reservoir. This ensures neutral pressure inside the ink tank. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Ink leakage bin and sensor 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The ink leakage bin is used to catch spilled ink from the ink supply system. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The ink leakage bin is positioned underneath the ink supply system. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The leakage bin can contain up to 2.65 liter of ink. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">Ink Leak Sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr ">02B18</compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal "> INK_LEAK_SE</compsignal></comp> is mounted in the leakage bin to detect the presence of ink in the leakage bin. 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><fig id="GUID-9F7110D4-344E-4675-B7C6-BC6807F2A5FE" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "> electrical components of the ink tanks</title><image href="GUID-7E7B73BE-FBF2-45FE-89CE-54E5418D12B1-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7E7B73BE-FBF2-45FE-89CE-54E5418D12B1-low.png"/></fig><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_1F27CB727ED74989B4250F44DFED7857" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="20*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50.50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="80*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row valign="top" class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Component 
